(17, 'The Apostle Peter: Redemption', , 'Action', 'English', '89 min', 'Nick Gillott, Karl Richards, Charlotte Walls', 'Steve Barker', 'Leif Films', 2016, 'R', 'John Rhys-Davies, Stephen Baldwin, Bobbie Phillips, Steve Byers, Dennis Andres', 'Tormented by his denial of Christ, Peter spent his life attempting to atone for his failures. Now as he faces certain death at the hand of Nero, will he falter again, his weakness betray him or will he rise up triumphant in his final moment?', 'The Apostle Peter followed Jesus zealously once he was called, but when faced with the darkest hour in history, Peter fell away and denied that he even knew his Lord.  Yet after His Resurrection, Jesus forgave Peter and made him the head of His church.  All his life, Peter sought to never forsake Christ again, so when faced with martyrdom, he only wanted to please his Lord and witness to those around himeven a skeptical Roman soldier who was seeking the truth.', NULL, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/43aUvmQw55Q', '4.00');
